        "created_at": "2026-01-21T17:14:50.406Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I don‚Äôt really understand why there is any confusion or criticism about top Gov officials using Signal. First, they‚Äôre using gov managed (enterprise grade) Apple hardware that is most likely in Lockdown mode at all times. Second, Signal offers one of the (if not the) strongest encryption in the world and is now quantum proof even for hack now harvest later protection. Third, despite each country most likely utilizing their own ‚Äúinternal‚Äù comms, Signal is universal and cross platform. Again, I do realize that govs develop and use their own secure systems for many things but for unclassified/casual convo between world leaders, I see Signal as entirely appropriate (as long as any group chat members are carefully verified lol)</p>\n<p>As users ourselves, we clearly trust the encryption and support Signal via funding, beta testing, promoting, etc.</p>\n<p>Am I missing something?</p>",
