      {
        "id": 283369,
        "name": "üëäüá∫üá∏üî•",
        "username": "Avitus",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/avitus/{size}/34172_2.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-23T22:06:56.266Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"ret_ff17\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"74380\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/ret_ff17/48/49655_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> ret_ff17:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I don‚Äôt really understand why there is any confusion or criticism about top Gov officials using Signal.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>When the discussion is not about anything classified or government-related, there is no reason for criticism. If the discussion is either of those things, at least in America, there are laws around how and when the discussion should take place. Deliberately having government-related conversations out of public view is shady dictatorship shit, and that includes all the in-person closed-door shit American politicians do.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"ret_ff17\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"74380\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/ret_ff17/48/49655_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> ret_ff17:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>First, they‚Äôre using gov managed (enterprise grade) Apple hardware that is most likely in Lockdown mode at all times.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I would not assume this for the Trump Administration. They‚Äôve proven their immeasurable incompetence beyond a reasonable doubt, on multiple occasions.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"ret_ff17\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"74380\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/ret_ff17/48/49655_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> ret_ff17:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Second, Signal offers one of the (if not the) strongest encryption in the world and is now quantum proof even for hack now harvest later protection.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>As stated above, there are laws around when and how certain discussions should happen. Signal is secure, <a href=\"https://www.politico.com/news/2025/04/02/inside-the-hazy-fractured-mess-of-signal-chats-in-the-government-00264466\">but it‚Äôs not authorized for sensitive government communication</a>. DoD and NSA policy strictly forbid its use for sensitive discussions.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"ret_ff17\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"74380\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/ret_ff17/48/49655_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> ret_ff17:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Third, despite each country most likely utilizing their own ‚Äúinternal‚Äù comms, Signal is universal and cross platform.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>The point of internal tools is that they‚Äôre vetted and independently secured by intelligence and defense agencies, not some consumer app anyone can use and is as secure as the organization running it. That‚Äôs why it was a significant problem that it was used to discuss sensitive, top secret military bombings of Yemeni civilians last year.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"ret_ff17\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"74380\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/ret_ff17/48/49655_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> ret_ff17:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Again, I do realize that govs develop and use their own secure systems for many things but for unclassified/casual convo between world leaders, I see Signal as entirely appropriate (as long as any group chat members are carefully verified lol)</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>It‚Äôs entirely inappropriate for the reasons I said above. Having conversations with international leaders and any other government-related discussion should not be happening outside of public view, because that‚Äôs dictatorship shit, not something that should be happening in a democracy.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"ret_ff17\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"74380\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/ret_ff17/48/49655_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> ret_ff17:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>As users ourselves, we clearly trust the encryption and support Signal via funding, beta testing, promoting, etc.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Because we as users can‚Äôt run our own infrastructure or don‚Äôt have the background to independently confirm what Signal claims. Supposedly we‚Äôve done our research and concluded, or someone that knows better has recommended it because it‚Äôs safe.</p>",
