        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/ret_ff17/{size}/49655_2.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-23T22:43:08.147Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I posed a legitimate question and there were some appropriate and helpful responses. Concerning the political bashing, I find that repulsive and not in line with the high standard I have experienced in this community for years now. I was <em>very</em> clear that I was referring to non-classified and casual comms- not anything related to nation security. Let‚Äôs keep the convo <strong>objective</strong> and leave the <em><strong>subjective</strong></em> political feelings out of things. Thank you.</p>\n<p>My point, again, was that Signal is secured in a way that no one can decrypt or ‚Äúhack‚Äù the messages. The weak link is always the users, rather intentional or inadvertently. The Signal Protocol is solid so if basic (and advanced) security protocols as well as common sense are followed, then there really is no risk whatsoever, right?</p>",
