        "created_at": "2026-01-25T15:44:03.046Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"ret_ff17\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"74380\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/ret_ff17/48/49655_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> ret_ff17:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Concerning the political bashing</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"ret_ff17\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"74380\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/ret_ff17/48/49655_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> ret_ff17:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Let‚Äôs keep the convo <strong>objective</strong> and leave the <em><strong>subjective</strong></em> political feelings out of things.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>What has been said that isn‚Äôt objective?</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"ret_ff17\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"74380\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/ret_ff17/48/49655_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> ret_ff17:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>My point, again, was that Signal is secured in a way that no one can decrypt or ‚Äúhack‚Äù the messages. The weak link is always the users, rather intentional or inadvertently. The Signal Protocol is solid so if basic (and advanced) security protocols as well as common sense are followed, then there really is no risk whatsoever, right?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>And this was addressed here:</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-username=\"Avitus\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"74380\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/avitus/48/34172_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Avitus:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"ret_ff17\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"74380\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/ret_ff17/48/49655_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> ret_ff17:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I don‚Äôt really understand why there is any confusion or criticism about top Gov officials using Signal.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>When the discussion is not about anything classified or government-related, there is no reason for criticism. If the discussion is either of those things, at least in America, there are laws around how and when the discussion should take place.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Here:</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-username=\"Avitus\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"74380\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/avitus/48/34172_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Avitus:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"ret_ff17\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"74380\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/ret_ff17/48/49655_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> ret_ff17:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Second, Signal offers one of the (if not the) strongest encryption in the world and is now quantum proof even for hack now harvest later protection.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>As stated above, there are laws around when and how certain discussions should happen. Signal is secure, <a href=\"https://www.politico.com/news/2025/04/02/inside-the-hazy-fractured-mess-of-signal-chats-in-the-government-00264466\">but it‚Äôs not authorized for sensitive government communication</a>. DoD and NSA policy strictly forbid its use for sensitive discussions.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>And here:</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-username=\"Avitus\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"74380\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/avitus/48/34172_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Avitus:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"ret_ff17\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"74380\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/ret_ff17/48/49655_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> ret_ff17:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Third, despite each country most likely utilizing their own ‚Äúinternal‚Äù comms, Signal is universal and cross platform.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>The point of internal tools is that they‚Äôre vetted and independently secured by intelligence and defense agencies, not some consumer app anyone can use and is as secure as the organization running it. That‚Äôs why it was a significant problem that it was used to discuss sensitive, top secret military bombings of Yemeni civilians last year.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>This is all specific to American national security expectations, but I imagine there‚Äôs not much difference in other countries that are supposed to be democracies.</p>",
